{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"55b6db2f-4cb4-445f-b0f4-c58bf8beb421","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since there's no existing code to edit, here's exactly what you need:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your ContentPage\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage\n    xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n    xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n    xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n    x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n    x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"Theme\" />\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Notifications\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Font Size\" />\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe only change is adding the `xmlns:vm` namespace import and the `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute. Every `{Binding}` on the page is now compiled against `SettingsViewModel` — a typo like `{Binding Thme}` becomes a **build error** instead of a silent runtime failure.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings are validated by the XAML compiler automatically. To ensure this is active:\n\n- **Confirm `x:DataType`** is set (as above).\n- **Keep XamlC enabled** (it's on by default in MAUI). You can be explicit in `AssemblyInfo.cs`:\n  ```csharp\n  [assembly: XamlCompilation(XamlCompilationOptions.Compile)]\n  ```\n- **Build the project** — any misspelled or wrong-type property will now surface as a compiler error:\n  ```\n  error XFC0045: Binding: Property \"Thme\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n  ```\n\n### Key gotchas\n\n| Scenario | Solution |\n|---|---|\n| Binding inside a `DataTemplate` | Add `x:DataType` to the `DataTemplate` itself |\n| Need a runtime binding (e.g. `BindingContext` swap) | Use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` to opt out locally |\n| Binding to a parent's context from a template | Use `Source={RelativeSource ...}` with a separate `x:DataType` |\n\nThat's it — the `x:DataType` attribute is the only XAML change needed. The compiler does the rest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c62d9394-f8fa-41c0-a76d-350a2b29feb7","outputTokens":655,"requestId":"9429:20A32C:13E396D:1647578:6A066FBF"},"id":"d1850ab2-262a-4726-bb11-4581b81fdde3","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:58:54.112Z","parentId":"b849ac99-22aa-4780-820f-b6beb355d5e1"}
